===Non-Fiction===
*''The African Image'' (1962; revised edition 1974)
*''Voices in the Whirlwind and Other Essays'' (1972)
*" ES'KIA" (2002) Publisher: Stainbank & Associates
*"ES'KIA Continued" (2004) Publisher: Stainbank & Associates
*''Bury Me At the Marketplace: Es'kia Mphahlele and Company - Letters 1943-2006'' (2010)

===Novels===
*''Father Come Home'' (1984)
*''Chirundu'' (1979)
*''The Wanderers'' (1969)

===Autobiography===
*''Afrika My Music'' (1984)
*''Down Second Avenue'' (1959)

===Short stories===
